fields.summary: Updated to the latest Appcelerator Studio Fails

comments.body:
Hi there...

Just wondering if I could get assistance on this issue, or any guidance?

Hi Christopher R McGuire ,

Thanks for your concern . Can you please share with us following information.
{code}
1. Appcelerator Studio Version
2. Node.js Version 
3. CLI Version  
4. node-appc Version   
{code}

Please try the following steps.

*Step 1*
{code}
1. Logout from studio clicking on the name at the bottom right corner
2. Logout from CLI using this command: appc logout â€“D
3. Open studio again
4.Log in

{code}

*Step 2*
{code}

1. Studio > Help > Install New Software > Available  Software Sites > Appcelerator Studio Updates 

Make Appcelerator Studio Updates & Eclipse Kepler Update Sites  checked .
{code}

Please feel free to contact  for further information.

Thanks

Hi there-

Thank you for the reply. For the above instructions, appc does not exist on my machine to trigger the CLI commands...titanium <command> does. Are these the same commands for CLI? (Sorry, total GUI user here). If so, titanium logout is deprecated, so not sure how to logout of the CLI.

I tried the above without logging out of the CLI, no luck.

As for versions:

Node.js:  v0.10.32
CLI version (via titanium -version command): v4.0.1
Studio Version: 3.4.1.201410281743

not sure how to get the node-appc version.

Talk soon
Chris

Hi ,

Please try this steps :

1. [Download & Install Appcelerator Studio|https://web.appcelerator.com/product/studio] Version 4.0.1 (Latest)
2. [Install the Appcelerator Command Line Tools (CLI)|https://web.appcelerator.com/product/cli] Version 4.0.2 (Latest).

Thanks

Hello,

I have tested this issue in updated environment. This is not a bug  for  latest Appcelerator version.  Not sure if this is still an issue for you.It doesn't appear to be based on our latest tests.

Please follow the steps and let us know:

*Appcelerator Studio > Help > Check for Appcelerator Studio Updates*



*Test Environments:*

CLI Version :4.1.3
Titanium SDK  Version:4.1.1.GA
Android: Google Galaxy Nexus:4.1.1 - API 16 - 720x1280
Appc Studio: Appcelerator Studio, build: 4.1.1.201507141126
Alloy: 1.7.6
Mac OS X,Version                     = 10.10.1



Thanks

Hi ,
I recommend you upgrade [studio|https://web.appcelerator.com/product/studio] to the latest  build and let us know if you get the error again.
Please take a look : [Errors While Updating|http://docs.appcelerator.com/platform/latest/#!/guide/Errors_While_Updating]

Thanks
